What are indenting rules for mla? 
ChatGPT said:
Great questionâ€”MLA formatting has specific indenting rules for different parts of your paper. Hereâ€™s a clear breakdown:

ğŸ“„ General Paragraph Indentation
Indent the first line of every paragraph by 0.5 inches.
Use the Tab key (not spaces) to create this indent.
Do not add extra space between paragraphsâ€”just indent the first line.
ğŸ”  Title and Heading
Do not indent the title. Center it.
Your heading (Name, Instructor, Course, Date) should be left-aligned with no indent.
ğŸ“š Works Cited (if required in future assignments)
Use a hanging indent:
First line of each citation is flush left.
All following lines in that entry are indented 0.5 inches.
Most word processors have a â€œhanging indentâ€ option under paragraph formatting.
Example Layout:
Amar Chowdhury
Professor Smith
ENG 102
17 April 2025

                          On Abbey, Berry, and the Death of the Local

        Iâ€™d wring your neck for juice if it was profitable.

        I think Wendell Berry and David S. Abbey might have gotten along...
